{"summary":"EPayments, a UK digital payments company, is officially winding down its business. \nThe payments firm had closed its doors in 2020 to try to improve its anti-crime controls following a request from UK regulators. ","author":["Kari McMahon","The Block"],"webName":"theblock.co","link":"https:\/\/www.theblock.co\/post\/169582\/uk-fintech-epayments-officially-closes-its-doors-following-fca-probe","publishDate":"2022-09-13T08:32:12","id":1608,"type":null,"title":"UK fintech EPayments officially closes its doors following FCA probe","category":["Payments and Banking"],"content":["<span class=\"TextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2Themed SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">EPayments<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">, a UK digital payments company, is officially closing its doors and winding down <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">its business after failing to satisfy regulators<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">, according to <\/span><\/span><a class=\"Hyperlink SCXW264409656 BCX0\" href=\"https:\/\/blog.epayments.com\/epayments-has-decided-to-close-the-business\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"TextRun Underlined SCXW264409656 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"none\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">a blog post<\/span><\/span><\/a><span class=\"TextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> yesterday.<\/span><\/span><span class=\"EOP SCXW264409656 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">&nbsp;<\/span>","<span class=\"TextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">The <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">company<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> shut<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> up shop <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">in 2020 at the request of the UK regulator,<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">, which<\/span> <span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">had <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">identified<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> \u201Cweaknesses\u201D in the<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> firm\u2019s<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> financial <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">crime controls.<\/span><\/span><span class=\"EOP SCXW257966133 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">&nbsp;<\/span>","<span class=\"TextRun SCXW141298648 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">Founded in 2011, <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2Themed SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">EPayments<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> was a payments services firm <a href=\"https:\/\/find-and-update.company-information.service.gov.uk\/company\/08134141\/filing-history?page=2\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">that provided<\/a>&nbsp;e-money wallets, pre-paid <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2Themed SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">Ma<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2Themed SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">stercards<\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\"> and payment and merchant services. The company had been registered and regulated by the FCA as an Electronic <\/span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">Money Institution (EMI).<\/span><\/span><span class=\"EOP SCXW141298648 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">&nbsp;<\/span>","<span data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">Since the FCA\u2019s request, the payments company has been working with regulators to improves its anti-crime controls.<\/span><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">&nbsp;<\/span>","<span data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">\u201CWe have over this period been working hard to ensure these are up to the required standard,\u201D the firm said in the blog&nbsp;post. \u201CBut in these extremely challenging and unprecedented global economic conditions, and with the business being restricted for such an extended period we can no longer sustain the business to build back to what the FCA require and a \u2018business as usual\u2019 state.\u201D<\/span><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">&nbsp;<\/span>","<span data-contrast=\"auto\" data-v-f87c67ca=\"\">Unable to build back the business, EPayments will now focus on winding down the business and providing refunds to customers. In 2019, the company held £127 million ($148 million) on behalf of clients, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com\/document-api-images-live.ch.gov.uk\/docs\/Mz9oCN-8HZnN7wYn8OS3cIvCUy5vlNKuEHuVIRKFmfM\/application-pdf?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAWRGBDBV3EQWE6YNP%2F20220913%2Feu-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&amp;X-Amz-Date=20220913T114129Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=60&amp;X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjEAoaCWV1LXdlc3QtMiJHMEUCIANdeWSy%2BzvDz29T%2Bifd6nwJJTZb%2F7AG3h3Eft%2FtRAu5AiEA2IGEAxIcP%2BZwVE8vgVt6pH%2Ftd2qn9Ila3alSHPBN2WQq1gQIo%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FARAEGgw0NDkyMjkwMzI4MjIiDBcNAEGTml5BcZTKMyqqBFpC5C7xWiVHXX2LvChZI6CymmF9vAZVtExJOMeJbua5em8ENiONXQWqKuVl3oUTzKZrSl1l8gamlKsJiAbVt0scaM44d%2Fe5bobeOtQz1wLBE1rnjoTAKaafT%2FWP7ADWf7yM2eRRgL07ICIp3cwwN5KgC7Me5I8aQfwIVu%2FvdDTTWEEVRF9GAmpvNrHeeFU58h%2FAvbeKcsBSG%2B3IoJTBrAvcXXK3NuV9NEcEj4zuqk0ltgWC4dTBXb4LQIxI17Qc7lM3mIglqjzZ1pCE0TcPwHLBP2qfm%2FNthW%2BWdqQJPRg4%2BX849wNY5wCLmmCScbXBeGPqZAlXO7%2BSC%2FzKzvyPIjhYANfzJ1Qvx1I9X6P4ArW90GjXKlmYHXQXZPCpBNdXzNoXPY8oStFolIFbZPUJ4rmklA%2BxjWipRyme6o%2FVT45x0RqfRD%2BdE9lMSf39fj